## Amplitude Analytics API Platform

Amplitude provides a comprehensive suite of REST APIs for analytics data ingestion, user management, data export, and platform configuration. The platform serves as a complete analytics solution with APIs spanning data collection, user behavior analysis, cohort management, and compliance operations.

## Product Architecture and Feature Relationships

The API ecosystem is organized around several core functional areas:

**Data Ingestion Layer:**
- **HTTP V2 API** (`/2/httpapi`) - Primary server-to-server event tracking endpoint
- **Batch Event Upload API** - Bulk data ingestion with 20MB payload limits
- **Identify API** (`/identify`) - User property management and ID mapping
- **Group Identify API** (`/groupidentify`) - Group-level property management for Accounts add-on
- **Attribution API** (`/attribution`) - Mobile advertising attribution tracking

**Data Export and Access:**
- **Export API** (`/api/2/export`) - Raw event data export with 4GB limits
- **Dashboard REST API** - Analytics query results in JSON format
- **User Profile API** (`profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile`) - Individual user profile retrieval

**User and Cohort Management:**
- **Behavioral Cohorts API** - Cohort CRUD operations with S3-based async downloads
- **User Mapping API** (`/usermap`) - Cross-project user ID aliasing for Portfolio add-on
- **SCIM 2.0 API** - Enterprise user provisioning and group management

**Configuration and Metadata:**
- **Taxonomy API** - Event schema management for Enterprise plans
- **Lookup Table APIs** (v1 deprecated, v3 current) - CSV-based property augmentation
- **Releases API** (`/api/2/release`) - Product release tracking and chart annotations
- **Chart Annotations API** (`/api/2/annotations`) - Timeline annotation management

**Compliance and Privacy:**
- **User Privacy API** (`/api/2/deletions/users`) - GDPR/CCPA data deletion
- **CCPA DSAR API** - Data subject access request processing

## Key Nomenclature and Definitions

**Core Identifiers:**
- `amplitude_id` - Amplitude's internal user identifier
- `user_id` - Customer-defined user identifier
- `device_id` - Device-specific identifier
- `session_id` - User session identifier
- `insert_id` - Event deduplication identifier

**Mobile Attribution IDs:**
- `idfa` - iOS Identifier for Advertiser
- `idfv` - iOS Identifier for Vendor
- `adid` - Google Android Advertising ID
- `android_app_set_id` - Android App Set ID

**Property Operations:**
- `$set` - Set property value
- `$setOnce` - Set property only if not already set
- `$add` - Add numeric value
- `$append` - Append to array
- `$prepend` - Prepend to array
- `$unset` - Remove property

**Data Structures:**
- `event_properties` - Event-specific attributes
- `user_properties` - User-level attributes
- `group_properties` - Group-level attributes (Accounts add-on)
- `event_type` - Event name/category

**Rate Limiting and Throttling:**
- EPS (Events Per Second) - Rate limiting metric
- EPDS/EPUS - Events Per Device/User per Second
- Cost-based rate limiting - Enterprise API consumption model

## Product Ecosystem Integration

The APIs integrate with Amplitude's broader analytics platform through several key mechanisms:

**Plan-Based Feature Access:**
- Growth/Enterprise plans unlock advanced APIs (Cohorts, Taxonomy)
- Portfolio add-on enables cross-project user mapping
- Accounts add-on provides group-level analytics
- Activation plan required for User Profile API

**Regional Data Residency:**
- Standard endpoints: `api2.amplitude.com`, `api.amplitude.com`
- EU residency: `api.eu.amplitude.com`
- Specialized endpoints: `profile-api.amplitude.com`, `data-api.amplitude.com`

**Authentication Patterns:**
- API Key authentication for data ingestion
- HTTP Basic authentication for configuration APIs
- Secret key authentication for User Profile API
- SCIM key authentication for provisioning

**Asynchronous Processing:**
- Three-step async pattern: POST request → status polling → file download
- Used by Cohorts, CCPA DSAR, and Export APIs
- S3 pre-signed URLs for large file transfers

## Primary API Endpoints and Operations

**Data Ingestion:**
```
POST api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi - Event tracking
POST api2.amplitude.com/batch - Bulk event upload
POST api2.amplitude.com/identify - User property updates
POST api2.amplitude.com/groupidentify - Group property updates
POST api2.amplitude.com/attribution - Attribution events
```

**Data Export:**
```
GET /api/2/export - Raw event data export
GET profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile - User profiles
GET /api/2/events/segmentation - Event segmentation analytics
```

**Management Operations:**
```
GET/POST /api/2/cohorts - Cohort management
POST /api/2/deletions/users - User data deletion
GET/POST/PUT/DELETE data-api.amplitude.com/api/3/lookup_table - Lookup tables
POST /api/2/release - Release tracking
```

The platform implements comprehensive rate limiting (typically 1000 events/second for ingestion, varying limits for other APIs), supports both real-time and batch processing patterns, and provides extensive error handling with HTTP status codes and detailed response messages.